Single-SignON

Single Sign-On (SSO) enables users to authenticate once and gain access to multiple applications and services without needing to log in again. SSO is crucial for reducing "login fatigue," which happens when users are repeatedly asked to authenticate for each application they use within the same system. For Azure AD B2C, SSO helps businesses provide seamless access to their suite of applications for customers, partners, and other external users by centralizing identity and session management.

) } export default SinglesignOn
